			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Mayors across the country have figured out the trick. The economy is slumping and the imperial federal government is writing blank checks. Where do we line up?</p>
<p>Barack Obama is going to save the planet by creating infrastructure projects and negate these recent job losses by &#8220;creating jobs&#8221;. The only problem is, if this <a href="http://usmayors.org/mainstreeteconomicrecovery/documents/mser-report-200812.pdf">recent report </a>of &#8220;ready-to-go infrastructure projects&#8221; by the U.S Conference of Mayors is any predictor of things to come our taxes will be tapped for a whole lot of nothing.</p>
<p>There&#8217;s a ton of projects in this list and I&#8217;m noticing a trend&#8230; the gap between dollars spent and jobs created is HUGE.</p>
<ul>
<li>a proposed &#8220;O&#8217;Malley Road Reconstruction&#8221; in Anchorage, Alaska, that will cost $30 million but provide 300 jobs.</li>
<li>Police Facility Solar Panels for Lake Havasu City, Arizona, for only $400,000 and 75 jobs.</li>
<li>Stormwater Settlement Ponds for Beloit, Wisconsin for <strong>$1.5 million</strong> and five jobs.</li>
<li>The storm sewer system in St. John, Indiana needs &#8220;additional capacity.&#8221; $275,000 and 15 jobs</li>
</ul>
<p>That&#8217;s 4 projects, <strong>$32,175,000</strong> spent and a whopping 395 Jobs created.</p>
<p>If the unemployment rate is 6.1%&#8230; you&#8217;ve just dropped that percentage by 0.002%</p>
<p>OUTSTANDING! Just imagine how many jobs we can create with all this money we don&#8217;t have.</p>
<p><strong>Updates in BOLD.</strong></p>
]]></content:encoded>
