		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.rightonblog.net/?p=1608</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[When this housing bubble mess started, politicians and community organizers were shouting from on high that the almighty federal government could easily fix the plight of these poor homeowners being faced with foreclosures on their beloved homes, if only they could be allowed to refinance or receive assistance.
Well, get ready for the shock of a [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>When this housing bubble mess started, politicians and community organizers were shouting from on high that the almighty federal government could easily fix the plight of these poor homeowners being faced with foreclosures on their beloved homes, if only they could be allowed to refinance or receive assistance.</p>
<p>Well, get ready for the shock of a lifetime&#8230; those people who had no business owning that house in the first place, are apparently RE-defaulting on their home loans even after being bailed out the first time. Information due out from the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency and the Office of Thrift Supervision (did you even KNOW there was such an office?) shows that more than 58% of those who received restructured mortgages to stave off foreclosure have re-defaulted on their loans. Brilliant!</p>
<p>When asked why this is happening, the OCC only had this to say, &#8220;We don&#8217;t know the answers yet, but these are the types of questions that we have begun asking our servicers in detail.&#8221;</p>
<p>You don&#8217;t know WHY people are re-defaulting on their loans? Send someone from the Office of Thrift Supervision over to investigate&#8230; once they&#8217;re done watching the BCS Championship on the 50&#8243; Flat Screen I&#8217;m sure they can scratch together some reason why these people can&#8217;t seem to scrape up the money for their mortgage payments.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m sorry, but I have zero sympathy with MOST people who cannot pay their bills. If you can&#8217;t afford it, you should not have it. End of story.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
			<wfw:commentRss>http://www.rightonblog.net/2008/12/more-help-for-foreclosures/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
